        <title>How can we help?</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;So a student is diagnosed dyslexic. It's a relief and it's the start of the path to progress. In the video you just watched, psychologist Si Collyjist* suggests we should not label dyslexia as a learning ability. Â Neil Mackay in &lt;em&gt;Dyslexia: Successful Inclusion in the Secondary School (BDA)&lt;/em&gt; says this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;If a child does not learn in the way in which we teach then we must teach him in the way in which he learns. Let dyslexia be looked at from a different angle, not as a learning disability but a different learning ability.&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What can we do on a practical level to support our dyslexic students?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Si Collyjist*&lt;/em&gt; Get it? A dyslexic wouldn't.&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
